%I A394621 #22 Apr 12 2026 23:56:08
%S A394621 4,5,9,10,13,14,21,22,26,33,34,42,45,46,49,50,54,62,66,69,70,74,78,82,
%T A394621 85,86,90,105,106,110,114,129,130,134,138,141,142,146,150,153,154,158,
%U A394621 162,166,170,174,178,182,186,194,198,201,202,206,210,214,218,222
%N A394621 Numbers k of the form k = p1 + p2 = x^2 + y^2 + p1^2, where p1 and p2 are primes, x, y are integers.
%C A394621 Values that allow simultaneous solution to both a two prime sum and Legendre's 3 square theorem with one of the primes forming one square.
%C A394621 It appears odd a(n) == 1 (mod 4) and odd a(n)-2 are prime.
%C A394621 Additionally the sequence frequently contains adjacent pairs a(n), a(n)+1.
%C A394621 Conjecture: odd a(n)-2 belong to A079739.
%C A394621 Conjecture: odd a(n)-4 belong to A001481.
%C A394621 Conjecture: even a(n) belong to A145979.
%H A394621 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Legendre%27s_three-square_theorem">Legendre's three-square theorem</a>.
%e A394621 26 = 3+23 = 1^2 + 4^2 + 3^2 and so 26 is a sequence term.
%e A394621 50 = 7+43 = 0^2 + 1^2 + 7^2 and so 50 is a sequence term.
%Y A394621 Cf. A000378, A079739, A001481, A004215, A071330, A145979.
%Y A394621 Subsequence of A042963.
%K A394621 nonn,new
%O A394621 1,1
